{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"It's a great honor to be here with you."},{"time":3000,"text":"The good news is"},{"time":6000,"text":"I'm very aware of my responsibilities to get you out of here"},{"time":9000,"text":"because I'm the only thing standing between you and the bar."},{"time":13000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":16000,"text":"And the good news is I don't have a prepared speech,"},{"time":19000,"text":"but I have a box of slides."},{"time":21000,"text":"I have some pictures that represent my life and what I do for a living."},{"time":27000,"text":"I've learned through experience"},{"time":30000,"text":"that people remember pictures long after they've forgotten words,"},{"time":35000,"text":"and so I hope you'll remember some of the pictures"},{"time":38000,"text":"I'm going to share with you for just a few minutes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44000,"text":"The whole story really starts"},{"time":46000,"text":"with me as a high school kid in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania,"},{"time":50000,"text":"in a tough neighborhood that everybody gave up on for dead."},{"time":53000,"text":"And on a Wednesday afternoon,"},{"time":56000,"text":"I was walking down the corridor of my high school"},{"time":60000,"text":"kind of minding my own business. And there was this artist teaching,"},{"time":66000,"text":"who made a great big old ceramic vessel,"},{"time":68000,"text":"and I happened to be looking in the door of the art room --"},{"time":71000,"text":"and if you've ever seen clay done, it's magic --"},{"time":73000,"text":"and I'd never seen anything like that before in my life."},{"time":78000,"text":"So, I walked in the art room and I said, \"What is that?\""},{"time":82000,"text":"And he said, \"Ceramics. And who are you?\""},{"time":84000,"text":"And I said, \"I'm Bill Strickland. I want you to teach me that.\""},{"time":87000,"text":"And he said, \"Well, get your homeroom teacher to sign a piece of paper"},{"time":91000,"text":"that says you can come here, and I'll teach it to you.\""},{"time":94000,"text":"And so for the remaining two years of my high school,"},{"time":97000,"text":"I cut all my classes."},{"time":98000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":99000,"text":"But I had the presence of mind"},{"time":101000,"text":"to give the teachers' classes that I cut the pottery that I made,"},{"time":105000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":106000,"text":"and they gave me passing grades."},{"time":109000,"text":"And that's how I got out of high school."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112000,"text":"And Mr. Ross said,"},{"time":114000,"text":"\"You're too smart to die and I don't want it on my conscience,"},{"time":119000,"text":"so I'm leaving this school and I'm taking you with me.\""},{"time":121000,"text":"And he drove me out to the University of Pittsburgh"},{"time":124000,"text":"where I filled out a college application and got in on probation."},{"time":128000,"text":"Well, I'm now a trustee of the university,"},{"time":131000,"text":"and at my installation ceremony I said,"},{"time":135000,"text":"\"I'm the guy who came from the neighborhood"},{"time":139000,"text":"who got into the place on probation."},{"time":142000,"text":"Don't give up on the poor kids, because you never know"},{"time":145000,"text":"what's going to happen to those children in life.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":149000,"text":"What I'm going to show you for a couple of minutes"},{"time":152000,"text":"is a facility that I built in the toughest neighborhood in Pittsburgh"},{"time":157000,"text":"with the highest crime rate."},{"time":159000,"text":"One is called Bidwell Training Center; it is a vocational school"},{"time":164000,"text":"for ex-steel workers and single parents and welfare mothers."},{"time":168000,"text":"You remember we used to make steel in Pittsburgh?"},{"time":170000,"text":"Well, we don't make any steel anymore,"},{"time":172000,"text":"and the people who used to make the steel"},{"time":174000,"text":"are having a very tough time of it."},{"time":177000,"text":"And I rebuild them and give them new life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180000,"text":"Manchester Craftsmen's Guild is named after my neighborhood."},{"time":184000,"text":"I was adopted"},{"time":187000,"text":"by the Bishop of the Episcopal Diocese during the riots,"},{"time":190000,"text":"and he donated a row house. And in that row house"},{"time":193000,"text":"I started Manchester Craftsmen's Guild,"},{"time":195000,"text":"and I learned very quickly that wherever there are Episcopalians,"},{"time":201000,"text":"there's money in very close proximity."},{"time":203000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":207000,"text":"And the Bishop adopted me as his kid."},{"time":212000,"text":"And last year I spoke at his memorial service"},{"time":216000,"text":"and wished him well in this life."},{"time":220000,"text":"I went out and hired a student of Frank Lloyd Wright, the architect,"},{"time":226000,"text":"and I asked him to build me a world class center"},{"time":229000,"text":"in the worst neighborhood in Pittsburgh."},{"time":232000,"text":"And my building was a scale model for the Pittsburgh airport."},{"time":236000,"text":"And when you come to Pittsburgh -- and you're all invited --"},{"time":238000,"text":"you'll be flying into the blown-up version of my building."},{"time":242000,"text":"That's the building."},{"time":244000,"text":"Built in a tough neighborhood where people have been given up for dead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249000,"text":"My view is that if you want to involve yourself"},{"time":252000,"text":"in the life of people who have been given up on,"},{"time":255000,"text":"you have to look like the solution and not the problem."},{"time":260000,"text":"As you can see, it has a fountain in the courtyard."},{"time":263000,"text":"And the reason it has a fountain in the courtyard is I wanted one"},{"time":267000,"text":"and I had the checkbook, so I bought one and put it there."},{"time":270000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":271000,"text":"And now that I'm giving speeches at conferences like TED,"},{"time":274000,"text":"I got put on the board of the Carnegie Museum."},{"time":278000,"text":"At a reception in their courtyard, I noticed that they had a fountain"},{"time":283000,"text":"because they think that the people who go to the museum deserve a fountain."},{"time":288000,"text":"Well, I think that welfare mothers and at-risk kids"},{"time":292000,"text":"and ex-steel workers deserve a fountain in their life."},{"time":295000,"text":"And so the first thing that you see in my center in the springtime"},{"time":298000,"text":"is water that greets you -- water is life and water of human possibility --"},{"time":304000,"text":"and it sets an attitude and expectation"},{"time":307000,"text":"about how you feel about people before you ever give them a speech."},{"time":312000,"text":"So, from that fountain I built this building."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318000,"text":"As you can see, it has world class art, and it's all my taste"},{"time":323000,"text":"because I raised all the money."},{"time":325000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":326000,"text":"I said to my boy, \"When you raise the money,"},{"time":329000,"text":"we'll put your taste on the wall.\""},{"time":332000,"text":"That we have quilts and clay and calligraphy"},{"time":335000,"text":"and everywhere your eye turns,"},{"time":337000,"text":"there's something beautiful looking back at you,"},{"time":339000,"text":"that's deliberate."},{"time":341000,"text":"That's intentional."},{"time":343000,"text":"In my view, it is this kind of world"},{"time":347000,"text":"that can redeem the soul of poor people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352000,"text":"We also created a boardroom,"},{"time":357000,"text":"and I hired a Japanese cabinetmaker from Kyoto, Japan,"},{"time":361000,"text":"and commissioned him to do 60 pieces of furniture for our building."},{"time":365000,"text":"We have since spun him off into his own business."},{"time":368000,"text":"He's making a ton of money doing custom furniture for rich people."},{"time":371000,"text":"And I got 60 pieces out of it for my school"},{"time":374000,"text":"because I felt that welfare moms and ex-steel workers"},{"time":377000,"text":"and single parents deserved to come to a school"},{"time":382000,"text":"where there was handcrafted furniture that greeted them every day."},{"time":385000,"text":"Because it sets a tone and an attitude about how you feel about people"},{"time":389000,"text":"long before you give them the speech."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392000,"text":"We even have flowers in the hallway, and they're not plastic."},{"time":398000,"text":"Those are real and they're in my building every day."},{"time":401000,"text":"And now that I've given lots of speeches,"},{"time":403000,"text":"we had a bunch of high school principals come and see me,"},{"time":406000,"text":"and they said, \"Mr. Strickland,"},{"time":408000,"text":"what an extraordinary story and what a great school."},{"time":411000,"text":"And we were particularly touched by the flowers"},{"time":414000,"text":"and we were curious as to how the flowers got there.\""},{"time":416000,"text":"I said, \"Well, I got in my car and I went out to the greenhouse"},{"time":419000,"text":"and I bought them and I brought them back and I put them there.\""},{"time":422000,"text":"You don't need a task force or a study group to buy flowers for your kids."},{"time":428000,"text":"What you need to know is that the children"},{"time":431000,"text":"and the adults deserve flowers in their life."},{"time":434000,"text":"The cost is incidental but the gesture is huge."},{"time":437000,"text":"And so in my building, which is full of sunlight and full of flowers,"},{"time":443000,"text":"we believe in hope and human possibilities."},{"time":445000,"text":"That happens to be at Christmas time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447000,"text":"And so the next thing you'll see is a million dollar kitchen"},{"time":453000,"text":"that was built by the Heinz company -- you've heard of them?"},{"time":457000,"text":"They did all right in the ketchup business."},{"time":460000,"text":"And I happen to know that company pretty well"},{"time":462000,"text":"because John Heinz, who was our U.S. senator --"},{"time":465000,"text":"who was tragically killed in a plane accident --"},{"time":468000,"text":"he had heard about my desire to build a new building,"},{"time":471000,"text":"because I had a cardboard box and I put it in a garbage bag"},{"time":474000,"text":"and I walking all over Pittsburgh trying to raise money for this site."},{"time":477000,"text":"And he called me into his office --"},{"time":479000,"text":"which is the equivalent of going to see the Wizard of Oz"},{"time":482000,"text":"(Laughter) --"},{"time":483000,"text":"and John Heinz had 600 million dollars, and at the time I had about 60 cents."},{"time":487000,"text":"And he said, \"But we've heard about you."},{"time":489000,"text":"We've heard about your work with the kids and the ex-steel workers,"},{"time":492000,"text":"and we're inclined to want to support your desire to build a new building."},{"time":497000,"text":"And you could do us a great service"},{"time":499000,"text":"if you would add a culinary program to your program.\""},{"time":504000,"text":"Because back then, we were building a trades program."},{"time":507000,"text":"He said, \"That way we could fulfill our affirmative action goals"},{"time":509000,"text":"for the Heinz company.\""},{"time":511000,"text":"I said, \"Senator, I'm reluctant to go into a field"},{"time":516000,"text":"that I don't know much about, but I promise you"},{"time":519000,"text":"that if you'll support my school, I'll get it built"},{"time":522000,"text":"and in a couple of years, I'll come back"},{"time":524000,"text":"and weigh out that program that you desire.\""},{"time":526000,"text":"And Senator Heinz sat very quietly and he said,"},{"time":530000,"text":"\"Well, what would your reaction be"},{"time":532000,"text":"if I said I'd give you a million dollars?\""},{"time":535000,"text":"I said, \"Senator, it appears that we're going into the food training business.\""},{"time":540000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":547000,"text":"And John Heinz did give me a million bucks."},{"time":550000,"text":"And most importantly,"},{"time":552000,"text":"he loaned me the head of research for the Heinz company."},{"time":555000,"text":"And we kind of borrowed the curriculum from the Culinary Institute of America,"},{"time":559000,"text":"which in their mind is kind of the Harvard of cooking schools,"},{"time":562000,"text":"and we created a gourmet cooks program for welfare mothers"},{"time":566000,"text":"in this million dollar kitchen in the middle of the inner city."},{"time":570000,"text":"And we've never looked back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572000,"text":"I would like to show you now some of the food"},{"time":576000,"text":"that these welfare mothers do in this million dollar kitchen."},{"time":580000,"text":"That happens to be our cafeteria line."},{"time":583000,"text":"That's puff pastry day. Why?"},{"time":586000,"text":"Because the students made puff pastry"},{"time":588000,"text":"and that's what the school ate every day."},{"time":590000,"text":"But the concept was that I wanted to take the stigma out of food."},{"time":595000,"text":"That good food's not for rich people --"},{"time":598000,"text":"good food's for everybody on the planet,"},{"time":600000,"text":"and there's no excuse why we all can't be eating it."},{"time":603000,"text":"So at my school, we subsidize a gourmet lunch program"},{"time":608000,"text":"for welfare mothers in the middle of the inner city"},{"time":611000,"text":"because we've discovered that it's good for their stomachs,"},{"time":613000,"text":"but it's better for their heads."},{"time":615000,"text":"Because I wanted to let them know every day of their life"},{"time":620000,"text":"that they have value at this place I call my center."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624000,"text":"We have students who sit together, black kids and white kids,"},{"time":630000,"text":"and what we've discovered is you can solve the race problem"},{"time":635000,"text":"by creating a world class environment,"},{"time":638000,"text":"because people will have a tendency to show you world class behavior"},{"time":642000,"text":"if you treat them in that way."},{"time":645000,"text":"These are examples of the food that welfare mothers are doing"},{"time":650000,"text":"after six months in the training program."},{"time":653000,"text":"No sophistication, no class, no dignity, no history."},{"time":659000,"text":"What we've discovered is the only thing wrong with poor people"},{"time":663000,"text":"is they don't have any money, which happens to be a curable condition."},{"time":669000,"text":"It's all in the way that you think about people"},{"time":672000,"text":"that often determines their behavior."},{"time":674000,"text":"That was done by a student after seven months in the program,"},{"time":678000,"text":"done by a very brilliant young woman"},{"time":682000,"text":"who was taught by our pastry chef."},{"time":684000,"text":"I've actually eaten seven of those baskets and they're very good."},{"time":687000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":688000,"text":"They have no calories."},{"time":690000,"text":"That's our dining room."},{"time":692000,"text":"It looks like your average high school cafeteria"},{"time":696000,"text":"in your average town in America."},{"time":699000,"text":"But this is my view of how students ought to be treated,"},{"time":703000,"text":"particularly once they have been pushed aside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":706000,"text":"We train pharmaceutical technicians for the pharmacy industry,"},{"time":712000,"text":"we train medical technicians for the medical industry,"},{"time":715000,"text":"and we train chemical technicians for companies"},{"time":719000,"text":"like Bayer and Calgon Carbon and Fisher Scientific and Exxon."},{"time":723000,"text":"And I will guarantee you that if you come to my center in Pittsburgh --"},{"time":729000,"text":"and you're all invited --"},{"time":731000,"text":"you'll see welfare mothers doing analytical chemistry"},{"time":733000,"text":"with logarithmic calculators"},{"time":735000,"text":"10 months from enrolling in the program."},{"time":738000,"text":"There is absolutely no reason why poor people"},{"time":743000,"text":"can't learn world class technology."},{"time":746000,"text":"What we've discovered is you have to give them flowers"},{"time":749000,"text":"and sunlight and food and expectations and Herbie's music,"},{"time":755000,"text":"and you can cure a spiritual cancer every time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":760000,"text":"We train corporate travel agents for the travel industry."},{"time":765000,"text":"We even teach people how to read."},{"time":768000,"text":"The kid with the red stripe was in the program two years ago --"},{"time":772000,"text":"he's now an instructor."},{"time":774000,"text":"And I have children with high school diplomas that they can't read."},{"time":779000,"text":"And so you must ask yourself the question:"},{"time":782000,"text":"how is it possible in the 21st century"},{"time":787000,"text":"that we graduate children from schools"},{"time":790000,"text":"who can't read the diplomas that they have in their hands?"},{"time":793000,"text":"The reason is that the system gets reimbursed"},{"time":796000,"text":"for the kids they spit out the other end, not the children who read."},{"time":801000,"text":"I can take these children and in 20 weeks,"},{"time":806000,"text":"demonstrated aptitude; I can get them high school equivalent."},{"time":810000,"text":"No big deal."},{"time":813000,"text":"That's our library with more handcrafted furniture."},{"time":819000,"text":"And this is the arts program I started in 1968."}]},{"cues":[{"time":823000,"text":"Remember I'm the black kid from the '60s who got his life saved with ceramics."},{"time":827000,"text":"Well, I went out and decided to reproduce my experience"},{"time":830000,"text":"with other kids in the neighborhood,"},{"time":832000,"text":"the theory being if you get kids flowers and you give them food"},{"time":836000,"text":"and you give them sunshine and enthusiasm,"},{"time":839000,"text":"you can bring them right back to life."},{"time":841000,"text":"I have 400 kids from the Pittsburgh public school system"},{"time":844000,"text":"that come to me every day of the week for arts education."},{"time":849000,"text":"And these are children who are flunking out of public school."},{"time":852000,"text":"And last year I put 88 percent of those kids in college"},{"time":855000,"text":"and I've averaged over 80 percent for 15 years."},{"time":859000,"text":"We've made a fascinating discovery:"},{"time":861000,"text":"there's nothing wrong with the kids"},{"time":864000,"text":"that affection and sunshine and food and enthusiasm"},{"time":869000,"text":"and Herbie's music can't cure."},{"time":872000,"text":"For that I won a big old plaque -- Man of the Year in Education."},{"time":876000,"text":"I beat out all the Ph.D.'s"},{"time":878000,"text":"because I figured that if you treat children like human beings,"},{"time":881000,"text":"it increases the likelihood they're going to behave that way."},{"time":884000,"text":"And why we can't institute that policy"},{"time":887000,"text":"in every school and in every city and every town"},{"time":893000,"text":"remains a mystery to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":896000,"text":"Let me show you what these people do."},{"time":899000,"text":"We have ceramics and photography and computer imaging."},{"time":903000,"text":"And these are all kids with no artistic ability, no talent,"},{"time":908000,"text":"no imagination. And we bring in the world's greatest artists --"},{"time":912000,"text":"Gordon Parks has been there, Chester Higgins has been there --"},{"time":915000,"text":"and what we've learned"},{"time":917000,"text":"is that the children will become like the people who teach them."},{"time":921000,"text":"In fact, I brought in a mosaic artist from the Vatican,"},{"time":925000,"text":"an African-American woman"},{"time":927000,"text":"who had studied the old Vatican mosaic techniques,"},{"time":930000,"text":"and let me show you what they did with the work."},{"time":934000,"text":"These were children who the whole world had given up on,"},{"time":938000,"text":"who were flunking out of public school,"},{"time":940000,"text":"and that's what they're capable of doing"},{"time":942000,"text":"with affection and sunlight and food and good music and confidence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":952000,"text":"We teach photography."},{"time":954000,"text":"And these are examples of some of the kids' work."},{"time":958000,"text":"That boy won a four-year scholarship"},{"time":961000,"text":"on the strength of that photograph."},{"time":964000,"text":"This is our gallery."},{"time":966000,"text":"We have a world class gallery"},{"time":968000,"text":"because we believe that poor kids need a world class gallery,"},{"time":972000,"text":"so I designed this thing."},{"time":974000,"text":"We have smoked salmon at the art openings,"},{"time":976000,"text":"we have a formal printed invitation,"},{"time":979000,"text":"and I even have figured out a way to get their parents to come."},{"time":982000,"text":"I couldn't buy a parent 15 years ago"},{"time":985000,"text":"so I hired a guy who got off on the Jesus big time."},{"time":989000,"text":"He was dragging guys out of bars"},{"time":991000,"text":"and saving those lives for the Lord."},{"time":993000,"text":"And I said, \"Bill, I want to hire you, man."},{"time":997000,"text":"You have to tone down the Jesus stuff a little bit,"},{"time":999000,"text":"but keep the enthusiasm."},{"time":1001000,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":1004000,"text":"I can't get these parents to come to the school.\""},{"time":1008000,"text":"He said, \"I'll get them to come to the school.\""},{"time":1010000,"text":"So, he jumped in the van, he went to Miss Jones' house and said,"},{"time":1012000,"text":"\"Miss Jones, I knew you wanted to come to your kid's art opening"},{"time":1015000,"text":"but you probably didn't have a ride."},{"time":1018000,"text":"So, I came to give you a ride.\""},{"time":1020000,"text":"And he got 10 parents and then 20 parents."},{"time":1023000,"text":"At the last show that we did, 200 parents showed up"},{"time":1027000,"text":"and we didn't pick up one parent."},{"time":1029000,"text":"Because now it's become socially not acceptable not to show up"},{"time":1034000,"text":"to support your children at the Manchester Craftsmen's Guild"},{"time":1037000,"text":"because people think you're bad parents."},{"time":1039000,"text":"And there is no statistical difference"},{"time":1041000,"text":"between the white parents and the black parents."},{"time":1045000,"text":"Mothers will go where their children are being celebrated,"},{"time":1050000,"text":"every time, every town, every city."},{"time":1056000,"text":"I wanted you to see this gallery because it's as good as it gets."},{"time":1064000,"text":"And by the time I cut these kids loose from high school,"},{"time":1067000,"text":"they've got four shows on their resume"},{"time":1070000,"text":"before they apply to college because it's all up here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1073000,"text":"You have to change the way that people see themselves"},{"time":1077000,"text":"before you can change their behavior."},{"time":1080000,"text":"And it's worked out pretty good up to this day."},{"time":1085000,"text":"I even stuck another room on the building, which I'd like to show you."},{"time":1091000,"text":"This is brand new."},{"time":1093000,"text":"We just got this slide done in time for the TED Conference."},{"time":1097000,"text":"I gave this little slide show at a place called the Silicon Valley"},{"time":1102000,"text":"and I did all right."},{"time":1104000,"text":"And the woman came out of the audience,"},{"time":1106000,"text":"she said, \"That was a great story"},{"time":1108000,"text":"and I was very impressed with your presentation."},{"time":1110000,"text":"My only criticism is your computers are getting a little bit old.\""},{"time":1113000,"text":"And I said, \"Well, what do you do for a living?\""},{"time":1116000,"text":"She said, \"Well, I work for a company called Hewlett-Packard.\""},{"time":1120000,"text":"And I said, \"You're in the computer business, is that right?\""},{"time":1123000,"text":"She said, \"Yes, sir.\""},{"time":1125000,"text":"And I said, \"Well, there's an easy solution to that problem.\""},{"time":1127000,"text":"Well, I'm very pleased to announce to you that HP"},{"time":1131000,"text":"and a furniture company called Steelcase"},{"time":1134000,"text":"have adopted us as a demonstration model for all of their technology"},{"time":1138000,"text":"and all their furniture for the United States of America."},{"time":1141000,"text":"And that's the room"},{"time":1143000,"text":"that's initiating the relationship."},{"time":1145000,"text":"We got it just done in time to show you,"},{"time":1147000,"text":"so it's kind of the world debut of our digital imaging center."},{"time":1151000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1152000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1160000,"text":"I only have a couple more slides,"},{"time":1162000,"text":"and this is where the story gets kind of interesting."},{"time":1165000,"text":"So, I just want you to listen up for a couple more minutes"},{"time":1168000,"text":"and you'll understand why he's there and I'm here."},{"time":1173000,"text":"In 1986, I had the presence of mind to stick a music hall"},{"time":1177000,"text":"on the north end of the building while I was building it."},{"time":1180000,"text":"And a guy named Dizzy Gillespie showed up to play there"},{"time":1185000,"text":"because he knew this man over here, Marty Ashby."},{"time":1189000,"text":"And I stood on that stage with Dizzy Gillespie on sound check"},{"time":1193000,"text":"on a Wednesday afternoon, and I said,"},{"time":1195000,"text":"\"Dizzy, why would you come to a black-run center"},{"time":1198000,"text":"in the middle of an industrial park with a high crime rate"},{"time":1202000,"text":"that doesn't even have a reputation in music?\""},{"time":1204000,"text":"He said, \"Because I heard you built the center"},{"time":1206000,"text":"and I didn't believe that you did it, and I wanted to see for myself."},{"time":1209000,"text":"And now that I have, I want to give you a gift.\""},{"time":1214000,"text":"I said, \"You're the gift.\""},{"time":1216000,"text":"He said, \"No, sir. You're the gift."},{"time":1218000,"text":"And I'm going to allow you to record the concert"},{"time":1220000,"text":"and I'm going to give you the music,"},{"time":1222000,"text":"and if you ever choose to sell it, you must sign an agreement"},{"time":1225000,"text":"that says the money will come back and support the school.\""},{"time":1227000,"text":"And I recorded Dizzy. And he died a year later,"},{"time":1232000,"text":"but not before telling a fellow named McCoy Tyner what we were doing."},{"time":1236000,"text":"And he showed up and said,"},{"time":1238000,"text":"\"Dizzy talking about you all over the country, man,"},{"time":1240000,"text":"and I want to help you.\""},{"time":1242000,"text":"And then a guy named Wynton Marsalis showed up."},{"time":1245000,"text":"Then a bass player named Ray Brown,"},{"time":1248000,"text":"and a fellow named Stanley Turrentine,"},{"time":1251000,"text":"and a piano player named Herbie Hancock,"},{"time":1254000,"text":"and a band called the Count Basie Orchestra,"},{"time":1260000,"text":"and a fellow named Tito Puente,"},{"time":1263000,"text":"and a guy named Gary Burton, and Shirley Horn, and Betty Carter,"},{"time":1268000,"text":"and Dakota Staton and Nancy Wilson"},{"time":1271000,"text":"all have come to this center in the middle of an industrial park"},{"time":1276000,"text":"to sold out audiences in the middle of the inner city."},{"time":1279000,"text":"And I'm very pleased to tell you that, with their permission,"},{"time":1283000,"text":"I have now accumulated 600 recordings"},{"time":1286000,"text":"of the greatest artists in the world,"},{"time":1288000,"text":"including Joe Williams, who died,"},{"time":1292000,"text":"but not before his last recording was done at my school."},{"time":1297000,"text":"And Joe Williams came up to me and he put his hand on my shoulder"},{"time":1307000,"text":"and he said, \"God's picked you, man, to do this work."},{"time":1315000,"text":"And I want my music to be with you.\""},{"time":1318000,"text":"And that worked out all right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1322000,"text":"When the Basie band came, the band got so excited about the school"},{"time":1327000,"text":"they voted to give me the rights to the music."},{"time":1330000,"text":"And I recorded it and we won something called a Grammy."},{"time":1335000,"text":"And like a fool, I didn't go to the ceremony"},{"time":1338000,"text":"because I didn't think we were going to win."},{"time":1340000,"text":"Well, we did win,"},{"time":1342000,"text":"and our name was literally in lights over Madison Square Garden."},{"time":1344000,"text":"Then the U.N. Jazz Orchestra dropped by and we recorded them"},{"time":1353000,"text":"and got nominated for a second Grammy back to back."},{"time":1358000,"text":"So, we've become one of the hot, young jazz recording studios"},{"time":1361000,"text":"in the United States of America"},{"time":1363000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1364000,"text":"in the middle of the inner city with a high crime rate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1370000,"text":"That's the place all filled up with Republicans."},{"time":1376000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1380000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1381000,"text":"If you'd have dropped a bomb on that room,"},{"time":1383000,"text":"you'd have wiped out all the money in Pennsylvania"},{"time":1385000,"text":"because it was all sitting there."},{"time":1387000,"text":"Including my mother and father, who lived long enough"},{"time":1390000,"text":"to see their kid build that building."},{"time":1393000,"text":"And there's Dizzy, just like I told you. He was there."},{"time":1397000,"text":"And he was there, Tito Puente."},{"time":1400000,"text":"And Pat Metheny and Jim Hall were there"},{"time":1403000,"text":"and they recorded with us."},{"time":1405000,"text":"And that was our first recording studio, which was the broom closet."},{"time":1410000,"text":"We put the mops in the hallway and re-engineered the thing"},{"time":1413000,"text":"and that's where we recorded the first Grammy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1416000,"text":"And this is our new facility, which is all video technology."},{"time":1420000,"text":"And that is a room that was built for a woman named Nancy Wilson,"},{"time":1424000,"text":"who recorded that album at our school last Christmas."},{"time":1432000,"text":"And any of you who happened to have been watching Oprah Winfrey"},{"time":1434000,"text":"on Christmas Day, he was there and Nancy was there"},{"time":1438000,"text":"singing excerpts from this album,"},{"time":1440000,"text":"the rights to which she donated to our school."},{"time":1444000,"text":"And I can now tell you with absolute certainty"},{"time":1446000,"text":"that an appearance on Oprah Winfrey will sell 10,000 CDs."},{"time":1451000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1453000,"text":"We are currently number four on the Billboard Charts,"},{"time":1456000,"text":"right behind Tony Bennett."},{"time":1458000,"text":"And I think we're going to be fine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1460000,"text":"This was burned out during the riots -- this is next to my building --"},{"time":1464000,"text":"and so I had another cardboard box built"},{"time":1467000,"text":"and I walked back out in the streets again."},{"time":1469000,"text":"And that's the building, and that's the model,"},{"time":1472000,"text":"and on the right's a high-tech greenhouse"},{"time":1475000,"text":"and in the middle's the medical technology building."},{"time":1477000,"text":"And I'm very pleased to tell you that the building's done."},{"time":1480000,"text":"It's also full of anchor tenants at 20 dollars a foot --"},{"time":1485000,"text":"triple that in the middle of the inner city."},{"time":1487000,"text":"And there's the fountain."},{"time":1489000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1491000,"text":"Every building has a fountain."},{"time":1493000,"text":"And the University of Pittsburgh Medical Center are anchor tenants"},{"time":1496000,"text":"and they took half the building,"},{"time":1498000,"text":"and we now train medical technicians through all their system."},{"time":1501000,"text":"And Mellon Bank's a tenant."},{"time":1503000,"text":"And I love them because they pay the rent on time."},{"time":1506000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1507000,"text":"And as a result of the association,"},{"time":1509000,"text":"I'm now a director of the Mellon Financial Corporation"},{"time":1512000,"text":"that bought Dreyfus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1517000,"text":"And this is in the process of being built as we speak."},{"time":1521000,"text":"Multiply that picture times four and you will see the greenhouse"},{"time":1526000,"text":"that's going to open in October this year"},{"time":1528000,"text":"because we're going to grow those flowers"},{"time":1532000,"text":"in the middle of the inner city."},{"time":1534000,"text":"And we're going to have high school kids"},{"time":1536000,"text":"growing Phalaenopsis orchids in the middle of the inner city."},{"time":1541000,"text":"And we have a handshake with one of the large retail grocers"},{"time":1545000,"text":"to sell our orchids in all 240 stores in six states."},{"time":1550000,"text":"And our partners are Zuma Canyon Orchids of Malibu, California,"},{"time":1554000,"text":"who are Hispanic."},{"time":1556000,"text":"So, the Hispanics and the black folks have formed a partnership"},{"time":1559000,"text":"to grow high technology orchids in the middle of the inner city."},{"time":1563000,"text":"And I told my United States senator"},{"time":1566000,"text":"that there was a very high probability"},{"time":1568000,"text":"that if he could find some funding for this,"},{"time":1570000,"text":"we would become a left-hand column in the Wall Street Journal,"},{"time":1574000,"text":"to which he readily agreed."},{"time":1576000,"text":"And we got the funding and we open in the fall."},{"time":1578000,"text":"And you ought to come and see it -- it's going to be a hell of a story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1581000,"text":"And this is what I want to do when I grow up."},{"time":1586000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1588000,"text":"The brown building is the one you guys have been looking at"},{"time":1591000,"text":"and I'll tell you where I made my big mistake."},{"time":1594000,"text":"I had a chance to buy this whole industrial park --"},{"time":1598000,"text":"which is less than 1,000 feet from the riverfront --"},{"time":1600000,"text":"for four million dollars and I didn't do it."},{"time":1604000,"text":"And I built the first building, and guess what happened?"},{"time":1608000,"text":"I appreciated the real estate values beyond everybody's expectations"},{"time":1612000,"text":"and the owners of the park turned me down for eight million dollars last year,"},{"time":1618000,"text":"and said, \"Mr. Strickland,"},{"time":1620000,"text":"you ought to get the Civic Leader of the Year Award"},{"time":1622000,"text":"because you've appreciated our property values"},{"time":1624000,"text":"beyond our wildest expectations."},{"time":1626000,"text":"Thank you very much for that.\""},{"time":1629000,"text":"The moral of the story is you must be prepared to act on your dreams,"},{"time":1634000,"text":"just in case they do come true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1637000,"text":"And finally, there's this picture."},{"time":1643000,"text":"This is in a place called San Francisco."},{"time":1646000,"text":"And the reason this picture's in here is"},{"time":1649000,"text":"I did this slide show a couple years ago at a big economics summit,"},{"time":1653000,"text":"and there was a fellow in the audience who came up to me."},{"time":1655000,"text":"He said, \"Man, that's a great story."},{"time":1657000,"text":"I want one of those.\""},{"time":1659000,"text":"I said, \"Well, I'm very flattered. What do you do for a living?\""},{"time":1662000,"text":"He says, \"I run the city of San Francisco."},{"time":1664000,"text":"My name's Willie Brown.\""},{"time":1667000,"text":"And so I kind of accepted the flattery and the praise"},{"time":1672000,"text":"and put it out of my mind."},{"time":1674000,"text":"And that weekend, I was going back home"},{"time":1676000,"text":"and Herbie Hancock was playing our center that night --"},{"time":1681000,"text":"first time I'd met him."},{"time":1683000,"text":"And he walked in and he says, \"What is this?\""},{"time":1686000,"text":"And I said, \"Herbie, this is my concept of a training center"},{"time":1690000,"text":"for poor people.\""},{"time":1692000,"text":"And he said, \"As God as my witness,"},{"time":1695000,"text":"I've had a center like this in my mind for 25 years and you've built it."},{"time":1699000,"text":"And now I really want to build one.\""},{"time":1701000,"text":"I said, \"Well, where would you build this thing?\""},{"time":1703000,"text":"He said, \"San Francisco.\""},{"time":1705000,"text":"I said, \"Any chance you know Willie Brown?\""},{"time":1708000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1710000,"text":"As a matter of fact he did know Willie Brown,"},{"time":1713000,"text":"and Willie Brown and Herbie and I had dinner four years ago,"},{"time":1716000,"text":"and we started drawing out that center on the tablecloth."},{"time":1719000,"text":"And Willie Brown said, \"As sure as I'm the mayor of San Francisco,"},{"time":1723000,"text":"I'm going to build this thing"},{"time":1725000,"text":"as a legacy to the poor people of this city.\""},{"time":1729000,"text":"And he got me five acres of land on San Francisco Bay"},{"time":1733000,"text":"and we got an architect and we got a general contractor"},{"time":1737000,"text":"and we got Herbie on the board,"},{"time":1740000,"text":"and our friends from HP, and our friends from Steelcase,"},{"time":1743000,"text":"and our friends from Cisco, and our friends from Wells Fargo"},{"time":1746000,"text":"and Genentech."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1748000,"text":"And along the way, I met this real short guy"},{"time":1752000,"text":"at my slide show in the Silicon Valley."},{"time":1756000,"text":"He came up to me afterwards,"},{"time":1758000,"text":"he said, \"Man, that's a fabulous story."},{"time":1761000,"text":"I want to help you.\""},{"time":1763000,"text":"And I said, \"Well, thank you very much for that."},{"time":1765000,"text":"What do you do for a living?\""},{"time":1767000,"text":"He said, \"Well, I built a company called eBay.\""},{"time":1771000,"text":"I said, \"Well, that's very nice."},{"time":1773000,"text":"Thanks very much, and give me your card and sometime we'll talk.\""},{"time":1776000,"text":"I didn't know eBay from that jar of water sitting on that piano,"},{"time":1781000,"text":"but I had the presence of mind to go back"},{"time":1783000,"text":"and talk to one of the techie kids at my center."},{"time":1786000,"text":"I said, \"Hey man, what is eBay?\""},{"time":1788000,"text":"He said, \"Well, that's the electronic commerce network.\""},{"time":1791000,"text":"I said, \"Well, I met the guy who built the thing"},{"time":1793000,"text":"and he left me his card.\""},{"time":1796000,"text":"So, I called him up on the phone and I said, \"Mr. Skoll,"},{"time":1799000,"text":"I've come to have a much deeper appreciation of who you are"},{"time":1803000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1808000,"text":"and I'd like to become your friend.\""},{"time":1811000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1814000,"text":"And Jeff and I did become friends,"},{"time":1817000,"text":"and he's organized a team of people"},{"time":1820000,"text":"and we're going to build this center."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1825000,"text":"And I went down into the neighborhood called Bayview-Hunters Point,"},{"time":1831000,"text":"and I said, \"The mayor sent me down here to work with you"},{"time":1835000,"text":"and I want to build a center with you,"},{"time":1838000,"text":"but I'm not going to build you anything if you don't want it."},{"time":1841000,"text":"And all I've got is a box of slides.\""},{"time":1844000,"text":"And so I stood up in front of 200 very angry, very disappointed people"},{"time":1850000,"text":"on a summer night, and the air conditioner had broken"},{"time":1853000,"text":"and it was 100 degrees outside,"},{"time":1857000,"text":"and I started showing these pictures."},{"time":1859000,"text":"And after about 10 pictures they all settled down."},{"time":1863000,"text":"And I ran the story and I said, \"What do you think?\""},{"time":1868000,"text":"And in the back of the room, a woman stood up and she said,"},{"time":1871000,"text":"\"In 35 years of living in this God forsaken place,"},{"time":1874000,"text":"you're the only person that's come down here and treated us with dignity."},{"time":1878000,"text":"I'm going with you, man.\""},{"time":1881000,"text":"And she turned that audience around on a pin."},{"time":1884000,"text":"And I promised these people that I was going to build this thing,"},{"time":1888000,"text":"and we're going to build it all right."},{"time":1890000,"text":"And I think we can get in the ground this year"},{"time":1893000,"text":"as the first replication of the center in Pittsburgh."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1897000,"text":"But I met a guy named Quincy Jones along the way"},{"time":1903000,"text":"and I showed him the box of slides."},{"time":1907000,"text":"And Quincy said, \"I want to help you, man."},{"time":1910000,"text":"Let's do one in L.A.\""},{"time":1914000,"text":"And so he's assembled a group of people."},{"time":1917000,"text":"And I've fallen in love with him,"},{"time":1919000,"text":"as I have with Herbie and with his music."},{"time":1923000,"text":"And Quincy said, \"Where did the idea for centers like this come from?\""},{"time":1929000,"text":"And I said, \"It came from your music, man."},{"time":1932000,"text":"Because Mr. Ross used to bring in your albums"},{"time":1935000,"text":"when I was 16 years old in the pottery class,"},{"time":1938000,"text":"when the world was all dark,"},{"time":1941000,"text":"and your music got me to the sunlight.\""},{"time":1945000,"text":"And I said, \"If I can follow that music,"},{"time":1947000,"text":"I'll get out into the sunlight and I'll be OK."},{"time":1951000,"text":"And if that's not true, how did I get here?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1956000,"text":"I want you all to know"},{"time":1960000,"text":"that I think the world is a place that's worth living."},{"time":1964000,"text":"I believe in you."},{"time":1968000,"text":"I believe in your hopes and your dreams,"},{"time":1972000,"text":"I believe in your intelligence"},{"time":1975000,"text":"and I believe in your enthusiasm."},{"time":1977000,"text":"And I'm tired of living like this,"},{"time":1980000,"text":"going into town after town with people standing around on corners"},{"time":1985000,"text":"with holes where eyes used to be, their spirits damaged."},{"time":1992000,"text":"We won't make it as a country unless we can turn this thing around."},{"time":1996000,"text":"In Pennsylvania it costs 60,000 dollars to keep people in jail,"},{"time":2002000,"text":"most of whom look like me."},{"time":2004000,"text":"It's 40,000 dollars to build the University of Pittsburgh Medical School."},{"time":2008000,"text":"It's 20,000 dollars cheaper to build a medical school than to keep people in jail."},{"time":2012000,"text":"Do the math -- it will never work."},{"time":2017000,"text":"I am banking on you"},{"time":2019000,"text":"and I'm banking on guys like Herbie and Quincy and Hackett and Richard"},{"time":2028000,"text":"and very decent people who still believe in something."},{"time":2034000,"text":"And I want to do this in my lifetime, in every city and in every town."},{"time":2043000,"text":"And I don't think I'm crazy."},{"time":2045000,"text":"I think we can get home on this thing"},{"time":2047000,"text":"and I think we can build these all over the country"},{"time":2050000,"text":"for less money than we're spending on prisons."},{"time":2054000,"text":"And I believe we can turn this whole story around"},{"time":2057000,"text":"to one of celebration and one of hope."},{"time":2061000,"text":"In my business it's very difficult work."},{"time":2064000,"text":"You're always fighting upstream like a salmon --"},{"time":2067000,"text":"never enough money, too much need --"},{"time":2070000,"text":"and so there is a tendency"},{"time":2072000,"text":"to have an occupational depression that accompanies my work."},{"time":2076000,"text":"And so I've figured out, over time, the solution to the depression:"},{"time":2082000,"text":"you make a friend in every town and you'll never be lonely."},{"time":2088000,"text":"And my hope is that I've made a few here tonight."},{"time":2093000,"text":"And thanks for listening to what I had to say."},{"time":2096000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}